Deaths - EPI2 Scenarios

Pragati Prasad

2020-11-20

Mean, Cumulative with 95% CI, and Averted per 100K

Scenario HP13

Base Scenario: R0 of 1.7 and “2009-like” severity multiplied by 2 for all age groups except 65+, which remains the same as 2009

library(ggsci)
library(reshape)
library(dplyr)
library(gridExtra)
library(ggplot2)
library(egg)
library(plyr)
library(tidyr)
library(knitr)
library(kableExtra)

path <- "../model-forecasts/"

team.folder <- c("Columbia/COL/EPI2/", "Northeastern/EPI2/", "UTAustin/", "UVirginia/", "Imperial/", "Columbia/COL2/EPI2/")
team.abbrev <- c("COL", "NEU", "UTA", "UVA", "IMP", "COL2")
file.types <-c("SymIllness", "Hosp", "Deaths", "AntiviralTX")
scn = "HP13_"
read_overall_mean <- function(scn){
  
  cols <- c("sm.mean", "sm.perc2p5", "sm.perc97p5")

  s <- read.csv(paste0(path,team.folder[1],scn,file.types[3],"_",team.abbrev[1],".csv"))
  death <- data.frame(c(s[which(s$Agegroup == "Overall" &
                                       s$Bin %in% cols),],
                             `team` = team.abbrev[1]))
  
  for(i in 2:6){
    
    if(i == 4){
      scn = gsub("HP", "HP_", scn)
    }
    if(i == 5){
      scn = gsub("_", "", scn)
    }
    if(i == 6){
      scn = paste0(scn, "_")
    }
    f = paste0(path,team.folder[i],scn,file.types[3],"_",team.abbrev[i],".csv")
    if(i == 5){
      f =  paste0(path,team.folder[i],scn,"Death",team.abbrev[i],".csv")
    }
    if(file.exists(f)){
      s <- read.csv(f)
      if(ncol(s) > 58){
        s <- s[-1]
      }
      death <- rbind.fill(death, 
                               data.frame(c(s[which(s$Agegroup == "Overall" & 
                                                      s$Bin %in% cols),],`team` = team.abbrev[i])))
    }
    
  }
  weeks <- paste0("Week",1:52)
  death$Cml[which(is.na(death$Cml))] <- death$cml[which(is.na(death$Cml))]
  cml <<- death[c("Cml", "team", "Bin")]
  
  long <- gather(death, week, illnesses, weeks, factor_key=TRUE)
  long$week <- as.integer(gsub("Week", "", long$week))
  
  cols <- c("Bin", "team", "week", "illnesses")
  long <- long[cols]
  long_wide <- spread(long, Bin, illnesses)
  
  return(long_wide)
}

long_HP13 <- read_overall_mean(scn = "HP13_")

ggplot(data = long_HP13, aes(x = week, y = sm.mean, group = team)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = team), lwd = 1.0) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = sm.perc2p5, ymax = sm.perc97p5, fill = team), alpha = 0.3,
              show.legend = FALSE)+
  ylab("Deaths per 100,000") +
  scale_color_nejm() +
  scale_fill_nejm()

table <- cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.mean"),]
table <- table[,-3]

table$lower <-  cml$Cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.perc2p5")]
table$upper <-  cml$Cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.perc97p5")]
table$Team <- table$team
table$`Cum. Deaths per 100K` <- table$Cml
table$`95% CI` <- paste0("(", round(table$lower, 2), ", ", round(table$upper, 2), ")")

rownames(table) <- NULL

knitr::kable(table[5:7], digits = 2, caption = "HP13, No Intervention", align=rep('c', 3)) %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover"))

COL2 39.15 (37.37, 41.07) 
table1 <- table


#Bar chart for age stratification
read_ages <- function(scn){
  
  cols <- c("sm.mean")

  s <- read.csv(paste0(path,team.folder[1],scn,file.types[3],"_",team.abbrev[1],".csv"))
  death <- data.frame(c(s[which(s$Agegroup != "Overall" &
                                       s$Bin %in% cols),],
                             `team` = team.abbrev[1]))
  
  for(i in 2:6){
    
    if(i == 4){
      scn = gsub("HP", "HP_", scn)
    }
    if(i == 5){
      scn = gsub("_", "", scn)
    }
    if(i == 6){
      scn = paste0(scn, "_")
    }
    f = paste0(path,team.folder[i],scn,file.types[3],"_",team.abbrev[i],".csv")
    if(i == 5){
      f =  paste0(path,team.folder[i],scn,"Death",team.abbrev[i],".csv")
    }
    if(file.exists(f)){
      s <- read.csv(f)
      if(ncol(s) > 58){
        s <- s[-1]
      }
      death <- rbind.fill(death, 
                               data.frame(c(s[which(s$Agegroup != "Overall" & 
                                                      s$Bin %in% cols),],`team` = team.abbrev[i])))
    }
    
  }
  weeks <- paste0("Week",1:52)
  death$Cml[which(is.na(death$Cml))] <- death$cml[which(is.na(death$Cml))]
  cml <- death[c("Cml", "team", "Bin", "Agegroup")]
  cml$Agegroup <- sub("yr", "years", cml$Agegroup)
  cml$Agegroup <- factor(x = cml$Agegroup, levels = c("0-4 years", "5-17 years", "18-49 years", "50-64 years", "65+ years"))
  
  return(cml)
}

ages_1 <- read_ages(scn = "HP13_")
ggplot(ages_1, aes(fill=Agegroup, y=Cml, x=team)) + 
  geom_bar(position="fill", stat="identity") +
  ylab("Percent")+
  scale_fill_d3()

HP14

VX1

“Early”: Vaccine available 100 days after September 1

scenario <- "HP14_"

long <- read_overall_mean(scn = scenario)

ggplot(data = long, aes(x = week, y = sm.mean, group = team)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = team), lwd = 1.0) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = sm.perc2p5, ymax = sm.perc97p5, fill = team), alpha = 0.3,
              show.legend = FALSE)+
  ylab("Deaths per 100,000") +
  scale_color_nejm() +
  scale_fill_nejm()

table <- cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.mean"),]
table <- table[,-3]

table$lower <-  cml$Cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.perc2p5")]
table$upper <-  cml$Cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.perc97p5")]
table$Team <- table$team
table$`Cum. Deaths per 100K` <- table$Cml
table$`95% CI` <- paste0("(", round(table$lower, 2), ", ", round(table$upper, 2), ")")

table$`Averted Deaths per 100K (HP13)` <- ifelse(table$Team %in% table1$Team, table1$`Cum. Deaths per 100K` - table$`Cum. Deaths per 100K`, NA)
table$`% Reduction in Burden (HP13)` <- ifelse(table$Team %in% table1$Team, 100 * (table1$`Cum. Deaths per 100K` - table$`Cum. Deaths per 100K`) / table1$`Cum. Deaths per 100K`, NA)

rownames(table) <- NULL

knitr::kable(table[5:9], digits = 2, caption = "HP14: Compared to HP13", align=rep('c', 4)) %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover"))
HP14: Compared to HP13
Team Cum. Deaths per 100K 95% CI Averted Deaths per 100K (HP13) % Reduction in Burden (HP13)
COL 43.93 (35.91, 51.31) 1.46 3.21
NEU 60.91 (60.83, 61.13) 0.02 0.04
UTA 68.36 (34.41, 88.12) 10.51 13.33
UVA 41.13 (33.46, 47.3) 0.21 0.50
IMP 0.10 (0.09, 0.11) 158.32 99.94
COL2 39.14 (37.35, 41.05) 0.01 0.03 
ages <- read_ages(scn = scenario)
ggplot(ages, aes(fill=Agegroup, y=Cml, x=team)) + 
  geom_bar(position="fill", stat="identity") +
  ylab("Percent")+
  scale_fill_d3()

averted <- data.frame(scenario = rep(scenario, nrow(table)),
                                     team = table$Team,
                                     reduction = table$`% Reduction in Burden (HP13)`)
averted_age <- data.frame(scenario = scenario,
                         team = ages$team,
                         agegroup = ages$Agegroup,
                         reduction = 100*(ages_1$Cml - ages$Cml) / ages_1$Cml )

HP21

VX1 & SC1 & AV

  • “Early”: Vaccine available 100 days after September 1
  • Weekly Symptomatic Prevalence > 1% trigger, early (VX1) vaccine availability reopening
  • Antivirals
scenario <- "HP21_"

long <- read_overall_mean(scn = scenario)

ggplot(data = long, aes(x = week, y = sm.mean, group = team)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = team), lwd = 1.0) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = sm.perc2p5, ymax = sm.perc97p5, fill = team), alpha = 0.3,
              show.legend = FALSE)+
  ylab("Deaths per 100,000") +
  scale_color_nejm() +
  scale_fill_nejm()

table <- cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.mean"),]
table <- table[,-3]

table$lower <-  cml$Cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.perc2p5")]
table$upper <-  cml$Cml[which(cml$Bin == "sm.perc97p5")]
table$Team <- table$team
table$`Cum. Deaths per 100K` <- table$Cml
table$`95% CI` <- paste0("(", round(table$lower, 2), ", ", round(table$upper, 2), ")")

table$`Averted Deaths per 100K (HP13)` <- ifelse(table$Team %in% table1$Team, table1$`Cum. Deaths per 100K` - table$`Cum. Deaths per 100K`, NA)
table$`% Reduction in Burden (HP13)` <- ifelse(table$Team %in% table1$Team, 100 * (table1$`Cum. Deaths per 100K` - table$`Cum. Deaths per 100K`) / table1$`Cum. Deaths per 100K`, NA)

rownames(table) <- NULL

knitr::kable(table[5:9], digits = 2, caption = "HP21: Compared to HP13", align=rep('c', 4)) %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover"))
